fresno (/ˈfrɛznoʊ/ frez-noh), the county seat of fresno county, is a city in the u.s. state of california.
it is approximately 220 miles (350 km) northwest of los angeles, 170 miles (270 km) south of the state capital, sacramento, or 185 miles (300 km) south of san francisco.
the name fresno means "ash tree" in spanish, and an ash leaf is featured on the city's flag.
